How to set better goals for 2022 💪🏼

You’ve probably been forced to do SMART goals at uni or work. Yes they’re annoying but honestly they DO make your goals much easier to achieve. 

Let’s take a vague goal like “I want to save money” and flesh it out with the SMART criteria to help you stay on track and measure your success. 

S - specific 

M - measurable 

A - achievable/attainable

R - relevant 

T - time bound 

So “I want to save money” becomes “By the end of 2022, I will have saved $5000, which I can track in my WeMoney account as a savings goal.”

By adding those extra details, you’re giving yourself boundaries in which to achieve your goal AND ways to do it and measure your success! 

What’s your SMART resolution for 2022? If it has to do with money, download @getwemoney for free to help track your progress! (Ad)

Do you know the secret to getting the perfect Positano pic? 🌊

Unlike some of my pics where I use editing magic to get rid of people in the background, this one truly is a clear shot! Unfortunately, you won’t be able to get that from the shore. 

For a truly insta worthy pic with no one in the background, plus to capture the perfect angle with the water and colourful houses in the background, you’ll need to get IN the water. I braved the swim out with my phone to take pics and I’m so happy I did! 

The beach is very pebbly, so your best bet is to kind of launch yourself into the water 😅 swim out about 10m and look back towards the cliffs, this is where you’re going to get the ICONIC Pinterest vibes. 

BONUS TIP - play around with different settings like Live Photos and 0.5 lense to help get a variety of photos. When you’re out there, you’re so focussed on staying afloat and posing for the pic that you probably won’t get a chance to review the pics till you’re back on land. Just take LOADS and hope you get THE shot 🙌🏼

If Positano is on your bucket list, SAVE this post 😍

BOTTOMLESS CAFE ALERT! 🚨 

Buy whatever you like for lunch and upgrade to the bottomless drinks package for $49pp which includes cocktails (fancy strong ones, NOT weak watered down jugs!), wine and beer for an hour and a half. 

I wasn’t expecting to find such a great hidden gem on Gertrude St in Fitzroy but @arcadiaongertrude manages to nail EVERY aspect of being a cafe AND bar…

✅ Cozy and cute vibes
✅ STRONG drinks
✅ Hearty comfort food for winter 
✅ A big variety on the menu 
✅ Charcuterie board 😍
✅ Friendly staff that are keen to have a chat 
✅ Easily accessible by public transport 
✅ CHEAP COCKTAILS!

I was truly blown away and will be coming back for an afternoon cocktail and snack for sure 🫶🏼

Another day, another attempt to not hate my winter wardrobe! 🥶

Currently living by the 3 Cs:

CUTE - adding fun accessories like ribbons and earrings to still bring some joy to the fit 🎀

COMFY - I’m going to be miserable if I’m not comfy and cosy! Prioritising staying warm by using layers, especially my subtle skin tone @paire thermals AND picking shoes that won’t hurt after an hour @skechersaustralia

Dopamine dressing doesn’t have to be a head to toe fluro outfit! It’s all about adding little elements that bring you joy 🌈✨

Obviously it can look different to everyone: for me it’s rainbows, sparkles and usually lots of pink. For you it might be a flowy silhouette or a pin representing your fave band or show. 

Here are my tips to slowly incorporate dopamine dressing into your everyday style:

👂🏼 Earrings! My absolute favourite accessories and easy to get funky shapes, colours and even pop culture references. I find the best ones at local markets. 

🕶️ Sunglasses - just cause it’s winter doesn’t mean you shouldn’t be stylish AND protect your eyes. I have some seriously groovy shades from @sportsgirl that jazz up my outfits. 

💄 Makeup! So you’re not quite ready to give up your neutrals in the wardrobe department: try adding some pizzazz with colourful and/or sparkly eyeshadow and lipgloss. 

🧷 Accessories like pins and keychains on your collar, belt or bag are a really fun way to show some personality too. I have to say I don’t get the labubu hype BUT it’s a great example of expressing your own personal style through small trinkets. 

The number 1 thing to remember is true style comes from confidence! Believe in your own taste, it’s okay to not be “on trend”. As long as you’re happy and comfy, that will shine through and make you look a million bucks 🤑

Is it worth going to see the @lego @starwars Exhibition at Melbourne Museum? 🌌🧱

📍 @melbournemuseum 
 📆 Until July 19
💰 $38 for adults, kids $24 ($5 discount for
members)

I think it depends how much of a fan you are. For serious Lego lovers and true Star Wars fanatics, I think yes! But $40 is quite expensive as a casual enjoyer. You do get discounted entry though if you’re already a Melbourne museum member.

I did really love that it was super interactive and you got to play and explore rather than just looking at impressive builds. They also did a really good job of managing the crowds so that there weren’t too many people in the space at one time and there was always room at the building stations.

I think most women will agree that shopping for jeans is a nightmare no matter your size 😭

I’ve been searching for a new pair of jeans this winter and it is NOT for the faint of heart. I hate that not only is every single brand different in their sizing but different styles within the same store are completely different measurements 🙄 

I’m very happy to announce that I actually have found a pair that I love which I’ll show you very soon but here are a few tips to make it a little bit easier :

👖 Ignore the numbers and just size up. I’m usually a 16 or 18 in pants depending on the brand, the material, the style etc. And honestly, I was in denial about just trying a 20. Like it’s not a crime to be a size 20!!! We all know women’s sizing is crazy anyway 

👖 Don’t rush! Don’t force yourself to buy jeans in the first place you look give yourself lots of time to explore different shops and if you come home empty-handed a few times it’s okay.

👖 Go alone. I know a shopping spree can be fun but when it comes to something as intimidating and personal as jeans, I personally think it’s less pressure to go by yourself so you can take as long as you like.

👖 Shop where the workers look like you. I know those girlies are just doing their jobs but seriously I love asking workers who have a similar body type to me what their favourite style is and trying that on. 

If you’re hunting for jeans this winter - GOOD LUCK 💙
